starvationevasion.common.messages

Enum Response

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Response>
      • starvationevasion.common.messages.Response
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Response>

    public enum Response
extends java.lang.Enum<Response>
implements java.io.Serializable
    Shea Polansky Possible server responses to client messages. The server *will* respond to every message with an instance of the Response class. The only exception to this is when the server has decided to forcibly disconnect a given client. The server may disconnect, with or without sending a notification, any client that sends three or more messages that result in error Responses in a given minute. Note that a message may be 'illegal' (e.g. attempting to play two vote-required policy cards in a specific turn or attempting to login with bad credentials) but correctly transmitted. In this case, a message of Response.OK will be transmitted to the client, followed by a more specific rejection message.
